place.name: THORPE ABBOTS
place.gazetteerText: THORPE-ABBOTS, a parish in Depwade district, Norfolk; 3¾ miles E of Diss r. station. Post town, Scole. Acres, 1,122. Real property, £1,819. Pop., 256. Houses, 55. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £305.* Patron, J. P. Reade, Esq. The church is good. Charities, £9. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
